heavy parchment as the envelope,

1259
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:05,920
when it was jerked sharply out 
of his hand by Uncle Vernon.

1260
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:06,800
"That's mine!"

1261
00:47:06,800 --> 00:47:09,040
said Harry, trying to snatch it back.

1262
00:47:09,040 --> 00:47:10,440
"Who'd be writing to you?"

1263
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:11,760
sneered Uncle Vernon,

1264
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:15,400
shaking the letter open with 
one hand and glancing at it.

1265
00:47:15,400 --> 00:47:19,040
His face went from red to green 
faster than a set of traffic lights.

1266
00:47:19,040 --> 00:47:20,560
And it didn't stop there.

1267
00:47:20,560 --> 00:47:23,680
Within seconds it was the 
grayish white of old porridge.

1268
00:47:23,680 --> 00:47:25,800
"P-P-Petunia!" he gasped.

1269
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:27,960
Dudley tried to grab the letter to read it,

1270
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:31,040
but Uncle Vernon held it high out of his reach.

1271
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:34,240
Aunt Petunia took it curiously 
and read the first line.

1272
00:47:34,240 --> 00:47:36,640
For a moment it looked as though she might faint.

1273
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:39,400
She clutched her throat and made a choking noise.

1274
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:42,080
"Vernon! Oh my goodness , Vernon!"

1275
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,360
They stared at each other,

1276
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:47,280
seeming to have forgotten that Harry 
and Dudley were still in the room.

1277
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:49,320
Dudley wasn't used to being ignored.

1278
00:47:49,320 --> 00:47:52,840
He gave his father a sharp tap on 
the head with his Smelting stick.

1279
00:47:52,840 --> 00:47:53,920
"I want to read that letter,"

1280
00:47:53,920 --> 00:47:55,920
he said loudly. want to read it,

1281
00:47:55,920 --> 00:47:57,560
" said Harry furiously, "

1282
00:47:57,560 --> 00:47:58,640
as it's mine."

1283
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:00,120
"Get out, both of you,"

1284
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:03,880
croaked Uncle Vernon, stuffing the 
letter back inside its envelope.

1285
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,200
Harry didn't move.

1286
00:48:05,200 --> 00:48:07,000
I WANT MY LETTER!" he shouted.

1287
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:07,960
"Let me see it!"

1288
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:09,240
demanded Dudley.

1289
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:09,920
"OUT!"

1290
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:11,200
roared Uncle Vernon,

1291
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:12,240
and he took both Harry

1292
00:48:12,240 --> 00:48:15,480
and Dudley by the scruffs of their 
necks and threw them into the hall,

1293
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:17,720
slamming the kitchen door behind them.

1294
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:21,080
Harry and Dudley promptly had 
a furious but silent fight over

1295
00:48:21,080 --> 00:48:22,640
who would listen at the keyhole;

1296
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:23,560
Dudley won,

1297
00:48:23,560 --> 00:48:26,320
so Harry, his glasses dangling from one ear,

1298
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:30,320
lay flat on his stomach to listen 
at the crack between door and floor.

1299
00:48:30,320 --> 00:48:31,120
"Vernon,"

1300
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:33,360
Aunt Petunia was saying in a quivering voice,

1301
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:34,760
"look at the address ,

1302
00:48:34,760 --> 00:48:37,040
how could they possibly know where he sleeps?

1303
00:48:37,040 --> 00:48:39,000
You don't think they're watching the house?"

1304
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,200
"Watching , spying , might be following us,"

1305
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:43,080
muttered Uncle Vernon wildly.

1306
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:44,920
"But what should we do, Vernon?

1307
00:48:44,920 --> 00:48:46,160
Should we write back?

1308
00:48:46,160 --> 00:48:47,260
Tell them we don't want ,

1309
00:48:47,260 --> 00:48:47,600
"

1310
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:52,040
Harry could see Uncle Vernon's shiny black 
shoes pacing up and down the kitchen.

1311
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:52,440
"No,"

1312
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:53,760
he said finally.

1313
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:55,320
"No, we'll ignore it.

1314
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:56,720
If they don't get an answer...

1315
00:48:57,600 --> 00:48:58,800
Yes, that's best...

1316
00:48:58,800 --> 00:49:00,680
we won't do anything....

1317
00:49:00,680 --> 00:49:01,560
"But , "

1318
00:49:01,560 --> 00:49:03,800
"I'm not having one in the house, Petunia!

1319
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:08,240
Didn't we swear when we took him in 
we'd stamp out that dangerous nonsense?"

1320
00:49:08,240 --> 00:49:10,120
That evening when he got back from work,

1321
00:49:10,120 --> 00:49:12,960
Uncle Vernon did something he'd never done before;

1322
00:49:12,960 --> 00:49:14,960
he visited Harry in his cupboard.

1323
00:49:14,960 --> 00:49:16,000
"Where's my letter?"

1324
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:19,640
said Harry, the moment Uncle Vernon 
had squeezed through the door.

1325
00:49:19,640 --> 00:49:20,920
"Who's writing to me?"

1326
00:49:20,920 --> 00:49:23,560
"No one. it was addressed to you by mistake,"

1327
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:25,240
said Uncle Vernon shortly.

1328
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:26,240
"I have burned it."

1329
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:27,560
"It was not a mistake,"

1330
00:49:27,560 --> 00:49:28,760
said Harry angrily,

1331
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:30,320
"it had my cupboard on it."

1332
00:49:30,320 --> 00:49:31,160
"SILENCE!"

1333
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:32,400
yelled Uncle Vernon,

1334
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:34,920
and a couple of spiders fell from the ceiling.

1335
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:38,600
He took a few deep breaths and 
then forced his face into a smile,

1336
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:40,680
which looked quite painful.

1337
00:49:40,680 --> 00:49:43,520
"Er , yes, Harry , about this cupboard.

1338
00:49:43,520 --> 00:49:45,880
Your aunt and I have been thinking...

1339
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:47,880
you're really getting a bit big for it...

1340
00:49:47,880 --> 00:49:51,920
we think it might be nice if you 
moved into Dudley's second bedroom.

1341
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:52,200
"Why?"

1342
00:49:52,200 --> 00:49:53,200
said Harry.

1343
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:54,400
"Don't ask questions!"

1344
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:55,640
snapped his uncle.

1345
00:49:55,640 --> 00:49:57,800
"Take this stuff upstairs, now."

1346
00:49:57,800 --> 00:50:02,320
The Dursleys' house had four bedrooms: 
one for Uncle Vernon and Aunt Petunia,

1347
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:05,200
one for visitors (usually Uncle Vernon's sister,

1348
00:50:05,200 --> 00:50:07,320
Marge), one where Dudley slept,

1349
00:50:07,320 --> 00:50:09,120
and one where Dudley kept all the toys

1350
00:50:09,120 --> 00:50:11,920
and things that wouldn't 
fit into his first bedroom.

1351
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:15,200
It only took Harry one trip 
upstairs to move everything he owned

1352
00:50:15,200 --> 00:50:16,720
from the cupboard to this room.

1353
00:50:16,720 --> 00:50:19,120
He sat down on the bed and stared around him.

1354
00:50:19,120 --> 00:50:21,160
Nearly everything in here was broken.

1355
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:24,320
The month-old video camera 
was lying on top of a small,

1356
00:50:24,320 --> 00:50:28,000
working tank Dudley had once driven 
over the next door neighbor's dog;

1357
00:50:28,000 --> 00:50:31,120
in the corner was Dudley's 
first-ever television set,

1358
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:34,920
which he'd put his foot through when 
his favorite program had been canceled;

1359
00:50:34,920 --> 00:50:36,520
there was a large birdcage,

1360
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:40,760
which had once held a parrot that Dudley 
had swapped at school for a real air rifle,

1361
00:50:40,760 --> 00:50:44,640
which was up on a shelf with the end 
all bent because Dudley had sat on it.

1362
00:50:44,640 --> 00:50:46,600
Other shelves were full of books.

1363
00:50:46,600 --> 00:50:50,920
They were the only things in the room that 
looked as though they'd never been touched.

1364
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:54,320
From downstairs came the sound 
of Dudley bawling at his mother,

1365
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:55,960
I don't want him in there...

1366
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:57,000
I need that room...

1367
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,560
make him get out...."

1368
00:50:58,560 --> 00:51:00,960
Harry sighed and stretched out on the bed.

1369
00:51:00,960 --> 00:51:03,520
Yesterday he'd have given anything to be up here.

1370
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:07,840
Today he'd rather be back in his cupboard 
with that letter than up here without it.

1371
00:51:07,840 --> 00:51:09,160
Next morning at breakfast,

1372
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:10,720
everyone was rather quiet.

1373
00:51:10,720 --> 00:51:12,200
Dudley was in shock.

1374
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:13,120
He'd screamed,

1375
00:51:13,120 --> 00:51:15,240
whacked his father with his Smelting stick,

1376
00:51:15,240 --> 00:51:16,600
been sick on purpose,

1377
00:51:16,600 --> 00:51:17,600
kicked his mother,

1378
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:20,120
and thrown his tortoise 
through the greenhouse roof,

1379
00:51:20,120 --> 00:51:22,160
and he still didn't have his room back.

1380
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:24,280
Harry was thinking about this time yesterday

1381
00:51:24,280 --> 00:51:26,920
and bitterly wishing he'd 
opened the letter in the hall.

1382
00:51:26,920 --> 00:51:30,360
Uncle Vernon and Aunt Petunia 
kept looking at each other darkly.

1383
00:51:30,360 --> 00:51:31,440
When the mail arrived,

1384
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:32,280
Uncle Vernon,

1385
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:34,360
who seemed to be trying to be nice to Harry,

1386
00:51:34,360 --> 00:51:36,280
made Dudley go and get it.

1387
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:40,120
They heard him banging things with his 
Smelting stick all the way down the hall.

1388
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:41,000
Then he shouted,

1389
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,760
"There's another one! 'Mr. H.

1390
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:45,520
Potter, The Smallest Bedroom,

1391
00:51:45,520 --> 00:51:47,558
4 Privet Drive ,

1392
00:51:47,558 --> 00:51:47,560
'"

1393
00:51:47,560 --> 00:51:48,800
With a strangled cry,

1394
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:51,880
Uncle Vernon leapt from his 
seat and ran down the hall,

1395
00:51:51,880 --> 00:51:53,440
Harry right behind him.

1396
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:57,160
Uncle Vernon had to wrestle Dudley to 
the ground to get the letter from him,

1397
00:51:57,160 --> 00:51:58,240
which was made difficult

1398
00:51:58,240 --> 00:52:02,560
by the fact that Harry had grabbed Uncle 
Vernon around the neck from behind.

1399
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:04,360
After a minute of confused fighting,

1400
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:07,240
in which everyone got hit a 
lot by the Smelting stick,

1401
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:08,920
Uncle Vernon straightened up,

1402
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:10,160
gasping for breath,

1403
00:52:10,160 --> 00:52:12,280
with Harry's letter clutched in his hand.

1404
00:52:12,280 --> 00:52:14,960
"Go to your cupboard , I mean, your bedroom,"

1405
00:52:14,960 --> 00:52:16,240
he wheezed at Harry.

1406
00:52:16,240 --> 00:52:18,320
"Dudley , go , just go."

1407
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:20,680
Harry walked round and round his new room.

1408
00:52:20,680 --> 00:52:23,160
Someone knew he had moved out of his cupboard

1409
00:52:23,160 --> 00:52:26,120
and they seemed to know he 
hadn't received his first letter.

1410
00:52:26,120 --> 00:52:28,040
Surely that meant they'd try again?

1411
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:30,480
And this time he'd make sure they didn't fail.

1412
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:31,600
He had a plan.

1413
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:35,040
The repaired alarm clock rang 
at six o'clock the next morning.

1414
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:37,800
Harry turned it off quickly and dressed silently.

1415
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:39,520
He mustn't wake the Dursleys.

1416
00:52:39,520 --> 00:52:42,720
He stole downstairs without 
turning on any of the lights.

1417
00:52:42,720 --> 00:52:45,840
He was going to wait for the postman 
on the corner of Privet Drive

1418
00:52:45,840 --> 00:52:48,320
and get the letters for number four first.

1419
00:52:48,320 --> 00:52:53,520
His heart hammered as he crept across 
the dark hall toward the front door ,

1420
00:52:53,520 --> 00:52:54,920
Harry leapt into the air;

1421
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:58,520
he'd trodden on something big 
and squashy on the doormat ,

1422
00:52:58,520 --> 00:52:59,680
something alive!

1423
00:52:59,680 --> 00:53:03,760
Lights clicked on upstairs and to his 
horror Harry realized that the big,

1424
00:53:03,760 --> 00:53:06,240
squashy something had been his uncle's face.

1425
00:53:06,240 --> 00:53:10,160
Uncle Vernon had been lying at the foot 
of the front door in a sleeping bag,

1426
00:53:10,160 --> 00:53:14,280
clearly making sure that Harry didn't 
do exactly what he'd been trying to do.

1427
00:53:14,280 --> 00:53:19,240
He shouted at Harry for about half an hour 
and then told him to go and make a cup of tea.

1428
00:53:19,240 --> 00:53:23,280
Harry shuffled miserably off into the 
kitchen and by the time he got back,

1429
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:24,680
the mail had arrived,

1430
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:26,560
right into Uncle Vernon's lap.

1431
00:53:26,560 --> 00:53:29,320
Harry could see three letters 
addressed in green ink.

1432
00:53:29,320 --> 00:53:30,920
I want , " he began,

1433
00:53:30,920 --> 00:53:34,760
