letters into pieces before his eyes.

1434
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:37,120
Uncle Vernon didnt go to work that day.

1435
00:53:37,120 --> 00:53:39,880
He stayed at home and nailed up the mail slot.

1436
00:53:39,880 --> 00:53:40,320
"See,"

1437
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:43,120
he explained to Aunt Petunia 
through a mouthful of nails,

1438
00:53:43,120 --> 00:53:45,440
"if they can't deliver them they'll just give up."

1439
00:53:45,440 --> 00:53:47,840
"I'm not sure that'll work, Vernon."

1440
00:53:47,840 --> 00:53:50,840
"Oh, these people's minds work in strange ways,

1441
00:53:50,840 --> 00:53:53,280
Petunia, they're not like you and me,"

1442
00:53:53,280 --> 00:53:54,440
said Uncle Vernon,

1443
00:53:54,440 --> 00:53:58,520
trying to knock in a nail with the piece of 
fruitcake Aunt Petunia had just brought him.

1444
00:53:58,520 --> 00:54:01,920
On Friday, no less than twelve 
letters arrived for Harry.

1445
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:05,200
As they couldn't go through the mail 
slot they had been pushed under the door,

1446
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:06,680
slotted through the sides,

1447
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:10,560
and a few even forced through the small 
window in the downstairs bathroom.

1448
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:12,640
Uncle Vernon stayed at home again.

1449
00:54:12,640 --> 00:54:14,000
After burning all the letters,

1450
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,640
he got out a hammer and nails

1451
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:20,160
and boarded up the cracks around the front 
and back doors so no one could go out.

1452
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:20,640
He hummed

1453
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:21,960
"Tiptoe Through the Tulips"

1454
00:54:21,960 --> 00:54:24,520
as he worked, and jumped at small noises.

1455
00:54:24,520 --> 00:54:25,360
On Saturday,

1456
00:54:25,360 --> 00:54:27,240
things began to get out of hand.

1457
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:29,960
Twenty-four letters to Harry 
found their way into the house,

1458
00:54:29,960 --> 00:54:32,760
rolled up and hidden inside 
each of the two dozen eggs

1459
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:37,280
that their very confused milkman had handed 
Aunt Petunia through the living room window.

1460
00:54:37,280 --> 00:54:40,760
While Uncle Vernon made furious 
telephone calls to the post office

1461
00:54:40,760 --> 00:54:43,640
and the dairy trying to 
find someone to complain to,

1462
00:54:43,640 --> 00:54:46,600
Aunt Petunia shredded the 
letters in her food processor.

1463
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:48,880
"Who on earth wants to talk to you this badly?"

1464
00:54:48,880 --> 00:54:50,960
Dudley asked Harry in amazement.

1465
00:54:50,960 --> 00:54:52,000
On Sunday morning,

1466
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:57,040
Uncle Vernon sat down at the breakfast table 
looking tired and rather ill, but happy.

1467
00:54:57,040 --> 00:54:58,400
"No post on Sundays,"

1468
00:54:58,400 --> 00:55:01,920
he reminded them cheerfully as he 
spread marmalade on his newspapers,

1469
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:03,720
"no damn letters today , "

1470
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:06,320
Something came whizzing down 
the kitchen chimney as he spoke

1471
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:08,760
and caught him sharply on the back of the head.

1472
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:09,720
Next moment,

1473
00:55:09,720 --> 00:55:13,680
thirty or forty letters came pelting 
out of the fireplace like bullets.

1474
00:55:13,680 --> 00:55:14,840
