his father had hit him round the head 
for holding them up while he tried

1495
00:56:01,840 --> 00:56:03,280
to pack his television,

1496
00:56:03,280 --> 00:56:06,120
VCR, and computer in his sports bag.

1497
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:07,120
They drove.

1498
00:56:07,120 --> 00:56:08,200
And they drove.

1499
00:56:08,200 --> 00:56:11,120
Even Aunt Petunia didn't dare 
ask where they were going.

1500
00:56:11,120 --> 00:56:13,840
Every now and then Uncle 
Vernon would take a sharp turn

1501
00:56:13,840 --> 00:56:16,600
and drive in the opposite direction for a while.

1502
00:56:16,600 --> 00:56:18,640
"Shake'em off... shake 'em off,"

1503
00:56:18,640 --> 00:56:20,480
he would mutter whenever he did this.

1504
00:56:20,480 --> 00:56:22,840
They didn't stop to eat or drink all day.

1505
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:24,720
By nightfall Dudley was howling.

1506
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,240
He'd never had such a bad day in his life.

1507
00:56:27,040 --> 00:56:28,000
He was hungry,

1508
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:31,040
he'd missed five television 
programs he'd wanted to see,

1509
00:56:31,040 --> 00:56:35,280
and he'd never gone so long without 
blowing up an alien on his computer.

1510
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:38,480
Uncle Vernon stopped at last 
outside a gloomy-looking hotel

1511
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:40,440
on the outskirts of a big city.

1512
00:56:40,440 --> 00:56:43,400
Dudley and Harry shared a 
room with twin beds and damp,

1513
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:44,640
musty sheets.

1514
00:56:44,640 --> 00:56:46,640
Dudley snored but Harry stayed awake,

1515
00:56:46,640 --> 00:56:48,000
sitting on the windowsill,

1516
00:56:48,000 --> 00:56:51,640
staring down at the lights of 
passing cars and wondering....

1517
00:56:51,640 --> 00:56:56,200
They ate stale cornflakes and cold tinned 
tomatoes on toast for breakfast the next day.

1518
00:56:56,200 --> 00:56:59,560
They had just finished when the owner 
of the hotel came over to their table.

1519
00:56:59,560 --> 00:57:00,320
"'Scuse me,

1520
00:57:00,320 --> 00:57:02,640
but is one of you Mr. H. Potter?

1521
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:05,480
Only I got about an 'undred 
of these at the front desk."

1522
00:57:05,480 --> 00:57:09,160
She held up a letter so they 
could read the green ink address:

1523
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,360
Mr. H. Potter

1524
00:57:10,360 --> 00:57:11,160
Room 17

1525
00:57:11,160 --> 00:57:12,200
Railview Hotel

1526
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:13,080
Cokeworth

1527
00:57:13,080 --> 00:57:17,120
Harry made a grab for the letter but Uncle 
Vernon knocked his hand out of the way.

1528
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:18,360
The woman stared.

1529
00:57:18,360 --> 00:57:19,200
"I'll take them,"

1530
00:57:19,200 --> 00:57:20,400
said Uncle Vernon,

1531
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:23,400
standing up quickly and following 
her from the dining room.

1532
00:57:23,400 --> 00:57:25,280
Wouldn't it be better just to go home,

1533
00:57:25,280 --> 00:57:27,840
dear?" Aunt Petunia suggested timidly,

1534
00:57:27,840 --> 00:57:28,840
hours later,

1535
00:57:28,840 --> 00:57:31,320
but Uncle Vernon didn't seem to hear her.

1536
00:57:31,320 --> 00:57:33,120
Exactly what he was looking for,

1537
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:34,240
none of them knew.

1538
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:36,560
He drove them into the middle of a forest,

1539
00:57:36,560 --> 00:57:38,120
got out, looked around,

1540
00:57:38,120 --> 00:57:39,240
shook his head,

1541
00:57:39,240 --> 00:57:40,560
got back in the car,

1542
00:57:40,560 --> 00:57:42,040
and off they went again.

1543
00:57:42,040 --> 00:57:44,720
The same thing happened in 
the middle of a plowed field,

1544
00:57:44,720 --> 00:57:46,760
halfway across a suspension bridge,

1545
00:57:46,760 --> 00:57:49,400
and at the top of a multilevel parking garage.

1546
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:51,520
"Daddy's gone mad, hasn't he?"

1547
00:57:51,520 --> 00:57:54,560
Dudley asked Aunt Petunia 
dully late that afternoon.

1548
00:57:54,560 --> 00:57:56,120
Uncle Vernon had parked at the coast,

1549
00:57:56,640 --> 00:57:58,480
locked them all inside the car,

1550
00:57:58,480 --> 00:57:59,720
and disappeared.

1551
00:57:59,720 --> 00:58:01,040
It started to rain.

1552
00:58:01,040 --> 00:58:03,280
Great drops beat on the roof of the car.

1553
00:58:03,280 --> 00:58:04,560
Dud ley sniveled.

1554
00:58:04,560 --> 00:58:05,200
"It's Monday,"

1555
00:58:05,200 --> 00:58:06,440
he told his mother.

1556
00:58:06,440 --> 00:58:08,520
"The Great Humberto's on tonight.

1557
00:58:08,520 --> 00:58:12,000
I want to stay somewhere 
with a television. " Monday.

1558
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:13,960
This reminded Harry of something.

1559
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:15,040
If it was Monday ,

1560
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:18,200
and you could usually count on 
Dudley to know the days the week,

1561
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:19,800
because of television ,

1562
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:20,520
then tomorrow,

1563
00:58:20,520 --> 00:58:23,080
Tuesday, was Harry's eleventh birthday.

1564
00:58:23,080 --> 00:58:26,200
Of course, his birthdays were never exactly fun ,

1565
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:31,440
last year, the Dursleys had given him a coat 
hanger and a pair of Uncle Vernon's old socks.

1566
00:58:31,440 --> 00:58:33,600
Still, you weren't eleven every day.

1567
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:36,280
Uncle Vernon was back and he was smiling.

1568
00:58:36,280 --> 00:58:38,120
He was also carrying a long,

1569
00:58:38,120 --> 00:58:42,080
thin package and didn't answer Aunt 
Petunia when she asked what he'd bought.

1570
00:58:42,080 --> 00:58:44,320
"Found the perfect place!" he said.

1571
00:58:44,320 --> 00:58:46,200
"Come on! Everyone out!"

1572
00:58:46,200 --> 00:58:48,440
It was very cold outside the car.

1573
00:58:48,440 --> 00:58:52,280
Uncle Vernon was pointing at what 
looked like a large rock way out at sea.

1574
00:58:52,280 --> 00:58:56,480
Perched on top of the rock was the most 
miserable little shack you could imagine.

1575
00:58:56,480 --> 00:58:57,560
One thing was certain,

1576
00:58:57,560 --> 00:58:59,840
there was no television in there.

1577
00:58:59,840 --> 00:59:01,720
"Storm forecast for tonight!"

1578
00:59:01,720 --> 00:59:05,520
said Uncle Vernon gleefully, 
clapping his hands together.

1579
00:59:05,520 --> 00:59:08,600
"And this gentleman's kindly 
agreed to lend us his boat!"

1580
00:59:08,600 --> 00:59:11,160
A toothless old man came ambling up to them,

1581
00:59:11,160 --> 00:59:13,600
pointing, with a rather wicked grin,

1582
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:17,040
at an old rowboat bobbing in 
the iron-gray water below them.

1583
00:59:17,040 --> 00:59:18,560
"I've already got us some rations,"

1584
00:59:18,560 --> 00:59:19,680
said Uncle Vernon,

1585
00:59:19,680 --> 00:59:20,920
"so all aboard!"

1586
00:59:20,920 --> 00:59:22,520
It was freezing in the boat.

1587
00:59:22,520 --> 00:59:27,120
Icy sea spray and rain crept down their 
necks and a chilly wind whipped their faces.

1588
00:59:27,120 --> 00:59:29,520
After what seemed like 
hours they reached the rock,

1589
00:59:29,520 --> 00:59:30,680
where Uncle Vernon,

1590
00:59:30,680 --> 00:59:31,960
slipping and sliding,

1591
00:59:31,960 --> 00:59:34,200
led the way to the broken-down house.

1592
00:59:34,200 --> 00:59:35,560
The inside was horrible;

1593
00:59:35,560 --> 00:59:37,520
it smelled strongly of seaweed,

1594
00:59:37,520 --> 00:59:39,960
the wind whistled through 
the gaps in the wooden walls,

1595
00:59:39,960 --> 00:59:42,360
and the fireplace was damp and empty.

1596
00:59:42,360 --> 00:59:44,040
There were only two rooms.

1597
00:59:44,040 --> 00:59:48,560
Uncle Vernon's rations turned out to be 
a bag of chips each and four bananas.

1598
00:59:48,560 --> 00:59:52,840
He tried to start a fire but the empty 
chip bags just smoked and shriveled up.

1599
00:59:52,840 --> 00:59:55,160
"Could do with some of those letters now, eh?"

1600
00:59:55,160 --> 00:59:56,040
he said cheerfully.

1601
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:58,480
He was in a very good mood.

1602
00:59:58,480 --> 01:00:01,280
Obviously he thought nobody stood 
a chance of reaching them here

1603
01:00:01,280 --> 01:00:03,040
in a storm to deliver mail.

1604
01:00:03,040 --> 01:00:05,000
Harry privately agreed,

1605
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:07,160
though the thought didn't cheer him up at all.

1606
01:00:07,160 --> 01:00:08,080
As night fell,

1607
01:00:08,080 --> 01:00:10,200
the promised storm blew up around them.

1608
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:13,200
Spray from the high waves 
splattered the walls of the hut

1609
01:00:13,200 --> 01:00:16,000
and a fierce wind rattled the filthy windows.

1610
01:00:16,000 --> 01:00:19,120
Aunt Petunia found a few moldy 
blankets in the second room

1611
01:00:19,120 --> 01:00:22,120
and made up a bed for Dudley 
on the moth-eaten sofa.

1612
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:25,120
She and Uncle Vernon went off 
to the lumpy bed next door,

1613
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:28,040
and Harry was left to find the 
softest bit of floor he could

1614
01:00:28,040 --> 01:00:29,920
and to curl up under the thinnest,

1615
01:00:29,920 --> 01:00:31,520
most ragged blanket.

1616
01:00:31,520 --> 01:00:35,080
The storm raged more and more 
ferociously as the night went on.

1617
01:00:35,080 --> 01:00:36,440
Harry couldn't sleep.

1618
01:00:36,440 --> 01:00:37,960
He shivered and turned over,

1619
01:00:37,960 --> 01:00:39,360
trying to get comfortable,

1620
01:00:39,360 --> 01:00:41,160
his stomach rumbling with hunger.

1621
01:00:41,160 --> 01:00:45,880
Dudley's snores were drowned by the low 
rolls of thunder that started near midnight.

1622
01:00:45,880 --> 01:00:47,840
The lighted dial of Dudley's watch,

1623
01:00:47,840 --> 01:00:50,840
which was dangling over the edge 
of the sofa on his fat wrist,

1624
01:00:50,840 --> 01:00:53,600
told Harry he'd be eleven in ten minutes' time.

1625
01:00:53,600 --> 01:00:56,040
He lay and watched his birthday tick nearer,

1626
01:00:56,040 --> 01:00:58,280
wondering if the Dursleys would remember at all,

1627
01:00:58,280 --> 01:01:00,440
wondering where the letter writer was now.

1628
01:01:00,440 --> 01:01:01,720
Five minutes to go.

1629
01:01:01,720 --> 01:01:03,800
Harry heard something creak outside.

1630
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:06,040
He hoped the roof wasn't going to fall in,

1631
01:01:06,040 --> 01:01:08,160
although he might be warmer if it did.

1632
01:01:08,160 --> 01:01:09,480
Four minutes to go.

1633
01:01:09,480 --> 01:01:12,240
Maybe the house in Privet Drive 
would be so full of letters

1634
01:01:12,240 --> 01:01:15,360
when they got back that he'd 
be able to steal one somehow.

1635
01:01:15,360 --> 01:01:16,680
Three minutes to go.

1636
01:01:16,680 --> 01:01:17,640
Was that the sea,

1637
01:01:17,640 --> 01:01:19,680
slapping hard on the rock like that?

1638
01:01:19,680 --> 01:01:22,960
And (two minutes to go) what 
was that funny crunching noise?

1639
01:01:22,960 --> 01:01:24,960
Was the rock crumbling into the sea?

1640
01:01:24,960 --> 01:01:27,480
One minute to go and he'd be eleven.

1641
01:01:27,480 --> 01:01:30,000
Thirty seconds... twenty ... ten...

1642
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:32,160
nine , maybe he'd wake Dudley up,

1643
01:01:32,160 --> 01:01:33,640
just to annoy him , three...

1644
01:01:33,640 --> 01:01:36,080
two... one... BOOM.

1645
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:38,800
The whole shack shivered 
and Harry sat bolt upright,

1646
01:01:38,800 --> 01:01:40,200
staring at the door.

1647
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:41,360
Someone was outside,

1648
01:01:41,360 --> 01:01:42,800
knocking to come in.

1649
01:01:42,800 --> 01:01:43,920
CHAPTER FOUR

1650
01:01:43,920 --> 01:01:45,360
THE KEEPER OF THE KEYS

1651
01:01:45,360 --> 01:01:48,680
BOOM. They knocked again. Dudley jerked awake.

1652
01:01:48,680 --> 01:01:49,720
"Where's the cannon?"

1653
01:01:49,720 --> 01:01:51,160
he said stupidly.

1654
01:01:51,160 --> 01:01:55,040
There was a crash behind them and Uncle 
Vernon came skidding into the room.

1655
01:01:55,040 --> 01:01:57,120
He was holding a rifle in his hands ,

1656
01:01:57,120 --> 01:01:59,000
now they knew what had been in the long,

1657
01:01:59,000 --> 01:02:01,040
thin package he had brought with them.

1658
01:02:01,040 --> 01:02:01,840
"Who's there?"

1659
01:02:01,840 --> 01:02:02,760
he shouted.

1660
01:02:02,760 --> 01:02:04,520
"I warn you , I'm armed!"

1661
01:02:04,520 --> 01:02:07,640
There was a pause. Then , SMASH!

1662
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:10,960
The door was hit with such force 
that it swung clean off its hinges

1663
01:02:10,960 --> 01:02:13,880
and with a deafening crash 
landed flat on the floor.

1664
01:02:13,880 --> 01:02:16,520
A giant of a man was standing in the doorway.

1665
01:02:16,520 --> 01:02:19,360
His face was almost completely hidden by a long,

1666
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:21,480
shaggy mane of hair and a wild,

1667
01:02:21,480 --> 01:02:22,560
tangled beard,

1668
01:02:22,560 --> 01:02:24,000
but you could make out his eyes,

1669
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:26,720
glinting like black beetles under all the hair.

1670
01:02:26,720 --> 01:02:28,760
The giant squeezed his way into the hut,

1671
01:02:28,760 --> 01:02:31,440
stooping so that his head 
just brushed the ceiling.

1672
01:02:31,440 --> 01:02:32,440
He bent down,

1673
01:02:32,440 --> 01:02:33,480
picked up the door,

1674
01:02:33,480 --> 01:02:35,880
and fitted it easily back into its frame.

1675
01:02:35,880 --> 01:02:38,440
The noise of the storm outside dropped a little.

1676
01:02:38,440 --> 01:02:40,000
He turned to look at them all.

1677
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:42,520
"Couldn't make us a cup o' tea, could yeh?

1678
01:02:42,520 --> 01:02:44,240
It's not been an easy journey..."

1679
01:02:44,240 --> 01:02:47,720
He strode over to the sofa where 
Dudley sat frozen with fear.

1680
01:02:47,720 --> 01:02:49,400
"Budge up, yeh great lump,"

1681
01:02:49,400 --> 01:02:50,600
said the stranger.

1682
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:53,400
Dudley squeaked and ran to hide behind his mother,

1683
01:02:53,400 --> 01:02:54,520
who was crouching,

1684
01:02:54,520 --> 01:02:57,000
terrified, behind Uncle Vernon.

1685
01:02:57,000 --> 01:02:58,200
"An' here's Harry!"

1686
01:02:58,200 --> 01:02:59,320
said the giant.

1687
01:02:59,320 --> 01:03:00,960
Harry looked up into the fierce,

1688
01:03:00,960 --> 01:03:05,720
wild, shadowy face and saw that the 
beetle eyes were crinkled in a smile.

1689
01:03:05,720 --> 01:03:08,080
"Las' time I saw you, you was only a baby,"

1690
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:09,160
said the giant.

1691
01:03:09,160 --> 01:03:13,440
"Yeh look a lot like yet dad, 
but yeh've got yet mom's eyes."

1692
01:03:13,440 --> 01:03:16,000
Uncle Vernon made a funny rasping noise.

1693
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:17,760
I demand that you leave at once, sit!

1694
01:03:17,760 --> 01:03:18,920
" he said. "

1695
01:03:18,920 --> 01:03:20,720
You are breaking and entering!"

1696
01:03:20,720 --> 01:03:23,920
"Ah, shut up, Dursley, yeh great prune,"

1697
01:03:23,920 --> 01:03:24,920
said the giant;

1698
01:03:24,920 --> 01:03:27,440
he reached over the back of the sofa,

1699
01:03:27,440 --> 01:03:29,800
jerked the gun out of Uncle Vernon's hands,

1700
01:03:29,800 --> 01:03:33,120
bent it into a knot as easily as 
if it had been made of rubber,

1701
01:03:33,120 --> 01:03:35,120
and threw it into a corner of the room.

1702
01:03:35,120 --> 01:03:39,120
Uncle Vernon made another funny 
noise, like a mouse being trodden on.

1703
01:03:39,120 --> 01:03:40,160
"Anyway , Harry,"

1704
01:03:40,160 --> 01:03:42,960
said the giant, turning his back on the Dursleys,

1705
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:44,840
"a very happy birthday to yeh.

1706
01:03:44,840 --> 01:03:46,360
Got summat fer yeh here ,

1707
01:03:46,360 --> 01:03:48,920
I mighta sat on it at some point,

1708
01:03:48,920 --> 01:03:50,480
but it'll taste all right."

1709
01:03:50,480 --> 01:03:55,480
From an inside pocket of his black 
overcoat he pulled a slightly squashed box.

1710
01:03:55,480 --> 01:03:57,760
Harry opened it with trembling fingers.

1711
01:03:57,760 --> 01:03:58,960
Inside was a large,

1712
01:03:58,960 --> 01:04:03,120
sticky chocolate cake with Happy Birthday 
Harry written on it in green icing.

1713
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:04,720
Harry looked up at the giant.

1714
01:04:04,720 --> 01:04:06,160
He meant to say thank you,

1715
01:04:06,160 --> 01:04:08,520
but the words got lost on the way to his mouth,

1716
01:04:08,520 --> 01:04:10,040
and what he said instead was,

1717
01:04:10,040 --> 01:04:11,000
"Who are you?"

1718
01:04:11,000 --> 01:04:12,320
The giant chuckled.

1719
01:04:12,320 --> 01:04:14,560
"True, I haven't introduced meself.

1720
01:04:14,560 --> 01:04:15,680
Rubeus Hagrid,

1721
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:18,560
Keeper of Keys and Grounds at Hogwarts."

1722
01:04:18,560 --> 01:04:21,840
He held out an enormous hand 
and shook Harry's whole arm.

1723
01:04:21,840 --> 01:04:23,800
"What about that tea then, eh?"

1724
01:04:23,800 --> 01:04:26,120
he said, rubbing his hands together.

1725
01:04:26,120 --> 01:04:29,760
"I'd not say no ter summat 
stronger if yeh've got it, mind."

1726
01:04:29,760 --> 01:04:33,960
His eyes fell on the empty grate with the 
shriveled chip bags in it and he snorted.

1727
01:04:33,960 --> 01:04:35,800
He bent down over the fireplace;

1728
01:04:35,800 --> 01:04:39,160
they couldn't see what he was doing 
but when he drew back a second later,

1729
01:04:39,160 --> 01:04:40,920
there was a roaring fire there.

1730
01:04:40,920 --> 01:04:43,120
It filled the whole damp hut with flickering light

1731
01:04:43,120 --> 01:04:47,320
and Harry felt the warmth wash over him 
as though he'd sunk into a hot bath.

1732
01:04:47,320 --> 01:04:49,440
The giant sat back down on the sofa,

1733
01:04:49,440 --> 01:04:51,040
which sagged under his weight,

1734
01:04:51,040 --> 01:04:55,720
and began taking all sorts of things out of 
the pockets of his coat: a copper kettle,

1735
01:04:55,720 --> 01:04:57,800
a squashy package of sausages,

1736
01:04:57,800 --> 01:04:59,560
a poker, a teapot,

1737
01:04:59,560 --> 01:05:01,160
several chipped mugs,

1738
01:05:01,160 --> 01:05:05,520
and a bottle of some amber liquid that he 
took a swig from before starting to make tea.

1739
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:09,000
Soon the hut was full of the sound 
and smell of sizzling sausage.

1740
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:11,520
Nobody said a thing while the giant was working,

