He put Harry's wand back into its 
box and wrapped it in brown paper,

3134
01:54:54,680 --> 01:54:55,560
still muttering,

3135
01:54:55,560 --> 01:54:57,680
"Curious... curious..

3136
01:54:57,680 --> 01:54:58,200
"Sorry,"

3137
01:54:58,200 --> 01:54:59,080
said Harry,

3138
01:54:59,080 --> 01:55:00,480
"but what's curious?"

3139
01:55:00,480 --> 01:55:03,400
Mr. Ollivander fixed Harry with his pale stare.

3140
01:55:03,400 --> 01:55:05,240
"I remember every wand I've ever sold,

3141
01:55:05,240 --> 01:55:06,440
Mr. Potter.

3142
01:55:06,440 --> 01:55:07,880
Every single wand.

3143
01:55:07,880 --> 01:55:11,560
It so happens that the phoenix 
whose tail feather is in your wand,

3144
01:55:11,560 --> 01:55:12,840
gave another feather ,

3145
01:55:12,840 --> 01:55:13,920
just one other.

3146
01:55:13,920 --> 01:55:18,640
It is very curious indeed that you should be 
destined for this wand when its brother why,

3147
01:55:18,640 --> 01:55:20,480
