force him to do anything,

3228
01:58:10,200 --> 01:58:11,220
or shout at him ,

3229
01:58:11,220 --> 01:58:13,760
in fact, they didn't speak to him at all.

3230
01:58:13,760 --> 01:58:14,920
Half terrified,

3231
01:58:14,920 --> 01:58:15,840
half furious,

3232
01:58:15,840 --> 01:58:18,720
they acted as though any chair 
with Harry in it were empty.

3233
01:58:18,720 --> 01:58:20,840
Although this was an improvement in many ways,

3234
01:58:20,840 --> 01:58:23,440
it did become a bit depressing after a while.

3235
01:58:23,440 --> 01:58:24,640
Harry kept to his room,

3236
01:58:24,640 --> 01:58:26,280
with his new owl for company.

3237
01:58:26,280 --> 01:58:28,040
He had decided to call her Hedwig,

3238
01:58:28,040 --> 01:58:30,600
a name he had found in A History of Magic.

3239
01:58:30,600 --> 01:58:32,720
His school books were very interesting.

3240
01:58:32,720 --> 01:58:35,040
He lay on his bed reading late into the night,

3241
01:58:35,040 --> 01:58:38,600
Hedwig swooping in and out of 
the open window as she pleased.

3242
01:58:38,600 --> 01:58:42,040
It was lucky that Aunt Petunia 
didn't come in to vacuum anymore,

3243
01:58:42,040 --> 01:58:44,600
because Hedwig kept bringing back dead mice.

3244
01:58:44,600 --> 01:58:46,560
Every night before he went to sleep,

3245
01:58:46,560 --> 01:58:50,200
Harry ticked off another day on the 
piece of paper he had pinned to the wall,

3246
01:58:50,200 --> 01:58:52,440
counting down to September the first.

3247
01:58:52,440 --> 01:58:55,480
On the last day of August he thought 
he'd better speak to his aunt

3248
01:58:55,480 --> 01:58:58,600
and uncle about getting to King's 
Cross station the next day,

3249
01:58:58,600 --> 01:59:02,520
so he went down to the living room where 
they were watching a quiz show on television.

3250
01:59:02,520 --> 01:59:04,960
He cleared his throat to 
let them know he was there,

3251
01:59:04,960 --> 01:59:07,440
and Dudley screamed and ran from the room.

3252
01:59:07,440 --> 01:59:09,160
"Er , Uncle Vernon?"

3253
01:59:09,160 --> 01:59:11,600
Uncle Vernon grunted to show he was listening.

3254
01:59:11,600 --> 01:59:15,400
"Er , I need to be at King's Cross 
tomorrow to , to go to Hogwarts."

3255
01:59:15,400 --> 01:59:17,160
Uncle Vernon grunted again.

3256
01:59:17,160 --> 01:59:19,360
"Would it be all right if you gave me a lift?"

3257
01:59:19,360 --> 01:59:22,160
Grunt. Harry supposed that meant yes.

3258
01:59:22,160 --> 01:59:22,880
"Thank you."

3259
01:59:22,880 --> 01:59:26,600
He was about to go back upstairs 
when Uncle Vernon actually spoke.

3260
01:59:26,600 --> 01:59:29,240
"Funny way to get to a wizards' school, the train.

3261
01:59:29,240 --> 01:59:31,120
Magic carpets all got punctures,

3262
01:59:31,120 --> 01:59:31,880
have they?"

3263
01:59:31,880 --> 01:59:33,520
Harry didn't say anything.

3264
01:59:33,520 --> 01:59:35,480
"Where is this school, anyway?"

3265
01:59:35,480 --> 01:59:36,160
"I don't know,"

3266
01:59:36,160 --> 01:59:37,080
said Harry,

3267
01:59:37,080 --> 01:59:39,080
realizing this for the first time.

3268
01:59:39,080 --> 01:59:42,200
He pulled the ticket Hagrid had 
given him out of his pocket.

3269
01:59:42,200 --> 01:59:47,120
"I just take the train from platform nine and 
three-quarters at eleven o'clock," he read.

3270
01:59:47,120 --> 01:59:48,960
His aunt and uncle stared.

3271
01:59:48,960 --> 01:59:50,160
"Platform what?"

3272
01:59:50,160 --> 01:59:52,040
"Nine and three-quarters."

3273
01:59:52,040 --> 01:59:52,920
"Don't talk rubbish,"

3274
01:59:52,920 --> 01:59:54,160
said Uncle Vernon.

3275
01:59:54,160 --> 01:59:56,840
"There is no platform nine and three-quarters."

3276
01:59:56,840 --> 01:59:58,000
"It's on my ticket."

3277
01:59:58,000 --> 01:59:58,720
"Barking,"

3278
01:59:58,720 --> 01:59:59,840
said Uncle Vernon,

3279
01:59:59,840 --> 02:00:00,800
"howling mad,

3280
02:00:00,800 --> 02:00:01,840
the lot of them.

3281
02:00:01,840 --> 02:00:02,800
You'll see.

3282
02:00:02,800 --> 02:00:04,000
You just wait.

3283
02:00:04,000 --> 02:00:06,360
All right, we'll take you to King's Cross.

3284
02:00:06,360 --> 02:00:08,320
We're going up to London tomorrow anyway,

3285
02:00:08,320 --> 02:00:09,680
or I wouldn't bother."

3286
02:00:09,680 --> 02:00:11,160
"Why are you going to London?"

3287
02:00:11,160 --> 02:00:13,800
Harry asked, trying to keep things friendly.

3288
02:00:13,800 --> 02:00:15,480
"Taking Dudley to the hospital,"

3289
02:00:15,480 --> 02:00:16,960
growled Uncle Vernon.

3290
02:00:16,960 --> 02:00:20,360
"Got to have that ruddy tail removed 
before he goes to Smeltings."

3291
02:00:20,360 --> 02:00:22,640
Harry woke at five o'clock the next morning

3292
02:00:22,640 --> 02:00:25,680
and was too excited and 
nervous to go back to sleep.

3293
02:00:25,680 --> 02:00:27,440
He got up and pulled on his jeans

3294
02:00:27,440 --> 02:00:30,520
because he didn't want to walk into 
the station in his wizard's robes ,

3295
02:00:30,520 --> 02:00:32,200
he'd change on the train.

3296
02:00:32,200 --> 02:00:36,080
He checked his Hogwarts list yet again 
to make sure he had everything he needed,

3297
02:00:36,080 --> 02:00:38,720
saw that Hedwig was shut safely in her cage,

3298
02:00:38,720 --> 02:00:40,080
and then paced the room,

3299
02:00:40,080 --> 02:00:42,000
waiting for the Dursleys to get up.

3300
02:00:42,000 --> 02:00:43,120
Two hours later,

3301
02:00:43,120 --> 02:00:44,200
Harry's huge,

3302
02:00:44,200 --> 02:00:47,000
heavy trunk had been loaded 
into the Dursleys' car,

3303
02:00:47,000 --> 02:00:50,120
Aunt Petunia had talked Dudley 
into sitting next to Harry,

3304
02:00:50,120 --> 02:00:51,440
and they had set off.

3305
02:00:51,440 --> 02:00:53,960
They reached King's Cross at half past ten.

3306
02:00:53,960 --> 02:00:58,680
Uncle Vernon dumped Harry's trunk onto a 
cart and wheeled it into the station for him.

3307
02:00:58,680 --> 02:01:02,520
Harry thought this was strangely 
kind until Uncle Vernon stopped dead,

3308
02:01:02,520 --> 02:01:05,880
facing the platforms with 
a nasty grin on his face.

3309
02:01:05,880 --> 02:01:07,720
"Well, there you are, boy.

3310
02:01:07,720 --> 02:01:08,920
Platform nine ,

3311
02:01:08,920 --> 02:01:09,880
platform ten.

3312
02:01:09,880 --> 02:01:12,000
Your platform should be somewhere in the middle,

3313
02:01:12,000 --> 02:01:13,720
but they don't seem to have built it yet,

3314
02:01:13,720 --> 02:01:14,520
do they?"

3315
02:01:14,520 --> 02:01:16,440
He was quite right, of course.

3316
02:01:16,440 --> 02:01:19,320
There was a big plastic 
number nine over one platform

3317
02:01:19,320 --> 02:01:22,320
and a big plastic number 
ten over the one next to it,

3318
02:01:22,320 --> 02:01:23,240
and in the middle,

3319
02:01:23,240 --> 02:01:24,360
nothing at all.

3320
02:01:24,360 --> 02:01:25,400
"Have a good term,"

3321
02:01:25,400 --> 02:01:28,160
said Uncle Vernon with an even nastier smile.

3322
02:01:28,160 --> 02:01:29,880
He left without another word.

3323
02:01:29,880 --> 02:01:32,520
Harry turned and saw the Dursleys drive away.

3324
02:01:32,520 --> 02:01:34,120
All three of them were laughing.

3325
02:01:34,120 --> 02:01:35,920
Harry's mouth went rather dry.

3326
02:01:35,920 --> 02:01:38,360
What on earth was he going to do?

3327
02:01:38,360 --> 02:01:40,840
He was starting to attract a lot of funny looks,

3328
02:01:40,840 --> 02:01:41,960
because of Hedwig.

3329
02:01:41,960 --> 02:01:43,360
He'd have to ask someone.

3330
02:01:43,360 --> 02:01:45,040
He stopped a passing guard,

3331
02:01:45,040 --> 02:01:48,200
but didn't dare mention platform 
nine and three-quarters.

3332
02:01:48,200 --> 02:01:50,080
The guard had never heard of Hogwarts and

3333
02:01:50,080 --> 02:01:53,440
when Harry couldn't even tell him 
what part of the country it was in,

3334
02:01:53,440 --> 02:01:54,960
he started to get annoyed,

3335
02:01:54,960 --> 02:01:57,440
as though Harry was being stupid on purpose.

3336
02:01:57,440 --> 02:01:58,560
Getting desperate,

3337
02:01:58,560 --> 02:02:01,480
Harry asked for the train 
that left at eleven o'clock,

3338
02:02:01,480 --> 02:02:03,280
but the guard said there wasn't one.

3339
02:02:03,280 --> 02:02:04,800
In the end the guard strode away,

3340
02:02:04,800 --> 02:02:06,840
muttering about time wasters.

3341
02:02:06,840 --> 02:02:09,360
Harry was now trying hard not to panic.

3342
02:02:09,360 --> 02:02:11,960
According to the large clock 
over the arrivals board,

3343
02:02:11,960 --> 02:02:16,840
he had ten minutes left to get on the train 
to Hogwarts and he had no idea how to do it;

3344
02:02:16,840 --> 02:02:20,720
he was stranded in the middle of a 
station with a trunk he could hardly lift,

3345
02:02:20,720 --> 02:02:22,640
a pocket full of wizard money,

3346
02:02:22,640 --> 02:02:23,920
and a large owl.

3347
02:02:23,920 --> 02:02:26,960
Hagrid must have forgotten to 
tell him something you had to do,

3348
02:02:26,960 --> 02:02:30,480
like tapping the third brick on 
the left to get into Diagon Alley.

3349
02:02:30,480 --> 02:02:32,240
He wondered if he should get out his wand

3350
02:02:32,240 --> 02:02:36,720
and start tapping the ticket inspector's 
stand between platforms nine and ten.

3351
02:02:36,720 --> 02:02:41,080
At that moment a group of people passed 
just behind him and he caught a few words of

3352
02:02:41,080 --> 02:02:41,900
what they were saying.

3353
02:02:41,900 --> 02:02:45,000
", packed with Muggles, of course , "

3354
02:02:45,000 --> 02:02:46,440
Harry swung round.

3355
02:02:46,440 --> 02:02:49,520
The speaker was a plump woman 
who was talking to four boys,

3356
02:02:49,520 --> 02:02:51,200
all with flaming red hair.

3357
02:02:51,200 --> 02:02:54,040
Each of them was pushing a trunk 
like Harry's in front of him ,

3358
02:02:54,040 --> 02:02:55,240
and they had an owl.

3359
02:02:55,240 --> 02:02:56,120
Heart hammering,

3360
02:02:56,120 --> 02:02:58,000
Harry pushed his cart after them.

3361
02:02:58,000 --> 02:02:59,600
They stopped and so did he,

3362
02:02:59,600 --> 02:03:01,960
just near enough to hear what they were saying.

3363
02:03:01,960 --> 02:03:03,920
"Now, what's the platform number?"

3364
02:03:03,920 --> 02:03:05,360
said the boys' mother.

3365
02:03:05,360 --> 02:03:06,920
"Nine and three-quarters!"

3366
02:03:06,920 --> 02:03:10,960
piped a small girl, also red-headed, 
who was holding her hand,

3367
02:03:10,960 --> 02:03:12,880
"Mom, can't I go... "

3368
02:03:12,880 --> 02:03:14,080
"You're not old enough,

3369
02:03:14,080 --> 02:03:16,000
Ginny, now be quiet.

3370
02:03:16,000 --> 02:03:17,480
All right, Percy,

3371
02:03:17,480 --> 02:03:19,280
you go first."

3372
02:03:19,280 --> 02:03:23,000
What looked like the oldest boy 
marched toward platforms nine and ten.

3373
02:03:23,000 --> 02:03:24,000
Harry watched,

3374
02:03:24,000 --> 02:03:26,280
careful not to blink in case he missed it ,

3375
02:03:26,280 --> 02:03:30,040
but just as the boy reached the dividing 
barrier between the two platforms,

3376
02:03:30,040 --> 02:03:33,040
a large crowd of tourists 
came swarming in front of him

3377
02:03:33,040 --> 02:03:35,760
and by the time the last 
backpack had cleared away,

3378
02:03:35,760 --> 02:03:37,160
the boy had vanished.

3379
02:03:37,160 --> 02:03:38,520
"Fred, you next,"

3380
02:03:38,520 --> 02:03:39,920
the plump woman said.

3381
02:03:39,920 --> 02:03:41,560
"I'm not Fred, I'm George,"

3382
02:03:41,560 --> 02:03:42,520
said the boy.

3383
02:03:42,520 --> 02:03:43,920
"Honestly, woman,

3384
02:03:43,920 --> 02:03:46,160
you call yourself our mother?

3385
02:03:46,160 --> 02:03:47,640
CarA you tell I'm George?"

3386
02:03:47,640 --> 02:03:49,560
"Sorry, George, dear."

3387
02:03:49,560 --> 02:03:51,480
"Only joking, I am Fred,"

3388
02:03:51,480 --> 02:03:52,480
said the boy,

3389
02:03:52,480 --> 02:03:53,640
and off he went.

3390
02:03:53,640 --> 02:03:56,200
His twin called after him to hurry up,

3391
02:03:56,200 --> 02:03:57,640
and he must have done so,

3392
02:03:57,640 --> 02:03:58,960
because a second later,

3393
02:03:58,960 --> 02:03:59,960
he had gone ,

3394
02:03:59,960 --> 02:04:01,320
but how had he done it?

3395
02:04:01,320 --> 02:04:05,480
Now the third brother was walking briskly 
toward the barrier he was almost there ,

3396
02:04:05,480 --> 02:04:06,920
and then, quite suddenly,

3397
02:04:06,920 --> 02:04:08,320
he wasn't anywhere.

3398
02:04:08,320 --> 02:04:09,960
There was nothing else for it.

3399
02:04:09,960 --> 02:04:10,600
"Excuse me,"

3400
02:04:10,600 --> 02:04:12,280
Harry said to the plump woman.

3401
02:04:12,280 --> 02:04:14,120
"Hello, dear," she said.

3402
02:04:14,120 --> 02:04:17,080
"First time at Hogwarts? Ron's new, too."

3403
02:04:17,080 --> 02:04:19,960
She pointed at the last and youngest of her sons.

3404
02:04:19,960 --> 02:04:20,920
He was tall,

3405
02:04:20,920 --> 02:04:22,520
thin, and gangling,

3406
02:04:22,520 --> 02:04:23,560
with freckles,

3407
02:04:23,560 --> 02:04:24,840
big hands and feet,

3408
02:04:24,840 --> 02:04:26,360
and a long nose.

3409
02:04:26,360 --> 02:04:26,680
"Yes,"

3410
02:04:26,680 --> 02:04:27,720
said Harry.

3411
02:04:27,720 --> 02:04:30,160
"The thing is , the thing 
is, I don't know how to , "

3412
02:04:30,160 --> 02:04:31,800
"How to get onto the platform?"

3413
02:04:31,800 --> 02:04:34,160
she said kindly, and Harry nodded.

3414
02:04:34,160 --> 02:04:35,720
"Not to worry," she said.

3415
02:04:35,720 --> 02:04:40,040
"All you have to do is walk straight at 
the barrier between platforms nine and ten.

3416
02:04:40,040 --> 02:04:42,920
Don't stop and don't be 
scared you'll crash into it,

3417
02:04:42,920 --> 02:04:44,360
that's very important.

3418
02:04:44,360 --> 02:04:46,720
Best do it at a bit of a run if you're nervous.

3419
02:04:46,720 --> 02:04:48,960
Go on, go now before Ron."

3420
02:04:48,960 --> 02:04:50,040
"Er , okay,"

3421
02:04:50,040 --> 02:04:50,960
said Harry.

3422
02:04:50,960 --> 02:04:53,960
He pushed his trolley around 
and stared at the barrier.

3423
02:04:53,960 --> 02:04:55,960
It looked very solid.

3424
02:04:55,960 --> 02:04:57,560
He started to walk toward it.

3425
02:04:57,560 --> 02:05:01,280
People jostled him on their 
way to platforms nine and ten.

3426
02:05:01,280 --> 02:05:02,840
Harry walked more quickly.

3427
02:05:02,840 --> 02:05:06,440
He was going to smash right into that 
barrier and then he'd be in trouble ,

3428
02:05:06,440 --> 02:05:08,200
leaning forward on his cart,

3429
02:05:08,200 --> 02:05:09,920
he broke into a heavy run ,

3430
02:05:09,920 --> 02:05:12,200
the barrier was coming nearer and nearer ,

3431
02:05:12,200 --> 02:05:13,760
he wouldn't be able to stop ,

3432
02:05:13,760 --> 02:05:15,400
the cart was out of control ,

3433
02:05:15,400 --> 02:05:16,960
he was a foot away ,

3434
02:05:16,960 --> 02:05:19,320
he closed his eyes ready for the crash ,

3435
02:05:19,320 --> 02:05:20,360
It didn't come...

3436
02:05:20,360 --> 02:05:21,440
he kept on running...

3437
02:05:21,440 --> 02:05:22,960
he opened his eyes.

3438
02:05:22,960 --> 02:05:26,800
A scarlet steam engine was waiting 
next to a platform packed with people.

3439
02:05:26,800 --> 02:05:29,200
A sign overhead said Hogwarts Express,

3440
02:05:29,200 --> 02:05:30,480
eleven O'clock.

3441
02:05:30,480 --> 02:05:34,800
Harry looked behind him and saw a wrought-iron 
archway where the barrier had been,

3442
02:05:34,800 --> 02:05:37,720
with the words Platform Nine 
and Three-Quarters on it,

3443
02:05:37,720 --> 02:05:38,760
He had done it.

3444
02:05:38,760 --> 02:05:42,160
Smoke from the engine drifted over 
the heads of the chattering crowd,

3445
02:05:42,160 --> 02:05:45,720
while cats of every color wound 
here and there between their legs.

3446
02:05:45,720 --> 02:05:49,240
Owls hooted to one another in a 
disgruntled sort of way over the babble

3447
02:05:49,240 --> 02:05:51,240
and the scraping of heavy trunks.

3448
02:05:51,240 --> 02:05:54,280
The first few carriages were 
already packed with students,

3449
02:05:54,280 --> 02:05:56,960
some hanging out of the window 
to talk to their families,

3450
02:05:56,960 --> 02:05:58,680
some fighting over seats.

3451
02:05:58,680 --> 02:06:02,400
Harry pushed his cart off down the 
platform in search of an empty seat.

3452
02:06:02,400 --> 02:06:04,440
He passed a round-faced boy who was saying,

3453
02:06:04,440 --> 02:06:06,880
"Gran, I've lost my toad again."

3454
02:06:06,880 --> 02:06:07,840
"Oh, Neville,"

3455
02:06:07,840 --> 02:06:09,560
he heard the old woman sigh.

3456
02:06:09,560 --> 02:06:12,840
A boy with dreadlocks was 
surrounded by a small crowd.

3457
02:06:12,840 --> 02:06:15,520
"Give us a look, Lee, go on."

3458
02:06:15,520 --> 02:06:17,720
The boy lifted the lid of a box in his arms,

3459
02:06:17,720 --> 02:06:23,360
and the people around him shrieked and yelled 
as something inside poked out a long, hairy leg.

3460
02:06:23,360 --> 02:06:27,000
Harry pressed on through the crowd until 
he found an empty compartment near the end

3461
02:06:27,000 --> 02:06:28,000
of the train.

3462
02:06:28,000 --> 02:06:29,840
He put Hedwig inside first

3463
02:06:29,840 --> 02:06:33,360
and then started to shove and heave 
his trunk toward the train door.

3464
02:06:33,360 --> 02:06:36,320
He tried to lift it up the steps 
but could hardly raise one end

3465
02:06:36,320 --> 02:06:39,520
and twice he dropped it painfully on his foot.

3466
02:06:39,520 --> 02:06:40,600
"Want a hand?"

3467
02:06:40,600 --> 02:06:44,560
It was one of the red-haired twins 
he'd followed through the barrier.

3468
02:06:44,560 --> 02:06:45,800
"Yes, please,"

3469
02:06:45,800 --> 02:06:46,960
Harry panted.

3470
02:06:46,960 --> 02:06:49,400
"Oy, Fred! C'mere and help!"

3471
02:06:49,400 --> 02:06:50,440
With the twins' help,

3472
02:06:50,440 --> 02:06:54,800
Harry's trunk was at last tucked 
away in a corner of the compartment.

3473
02:06:54,800 --> 02:06:55,280
"Thanks,"

3474
02:06:55,280 --> 02:06:58,280
said Harry, pushing his 
sweaty hair out of his eyes.

3475
02:06:58,280 --> 02:06:59,040
"What's that?"

3476
02:06:59,040 --> 02:07:02,600
said one of the twins suddenly, 
pointing at Harry's lightning scar.

3477
02:07:02,600 --> 02:07:03,280
