3980
02:24:12,960 --> 02:24:14,040
And he was off,

3981
02:24:14,040 --> 02:24:17,800
explaining all about the four balls 
and the positions of the seven players,

3982
02:24:17,800 --> 02:24:21,680
describing famous games he'd been to with his 
brothers and the broomstick he'd like to get

3983
02:24:21,680 --> 02:24:22,880
if he had the money.

3984
02:24:22,880 --> 02:24:25,520
He was just taking Harry through 
the finer points of the game

3985
02:24:25,520 --> 02:24:28,081
when the compartment door slid open yet again,

3986
02:24:28,080 --> 02:24:29,920
but it wasn't Neville the toadless boy,

3987
02:24:29,920 --> 02:24:32,560
or Hermione Granger this time.

3988
02:24:32,560 --> 02:24:33,640
Three boys entered,

3989
02:24:33,640 --> 02:24:35,280
and Harry recognized the middle one

3990
02:24:35,279 --> 02:24:39,359
at once: it was the pale boy 
from Madam Malkin's robe shop.

3991
02:24:39,359 --> 02:24:43,920
He was looking at Harry with a lot more 
interest than he'd shown back in Diagon Alley.

3992
02:24:43,920 --> 02:24:45,720
"Is it true?" he said.

3993
02:24:45,720 --> 02:24:49,360
"They're saying all down the train that 
Harry Potter's in this compartment.

3994
02:24:49,359 --> 02:24:50,000
So it's you,

3995
02:24:50,000 --> 02:24:50,319
is it?"

3996
02:24:50,840 --> 02:24:51,160
"Yes,"

3997
02:24:51,160 --> 02:24:52,120
said Harry.

3998
02:24:52,120 --> 02:24:54,080
He was looking at the other boys.

3999
02:24:54,080 --> 02:24:57,000
Both of them were thickset 
and looked extremely mean.

4000
02:24:57,000 --> 02:24:58,880
Standing on either side of the pale boy,

4001
02:24:58,880 --> 02:25:00,680
they looked like bodyguards.

4002
02:25:00,680 --> 02:25:03,120
"Oh, this is Crabbe and this is Goyle,"

4003
02:25:03,120 --> 02:25:06,559
said the pale boy carelessly, 
noticing where Harry was looking.

4004
02:25:06,560 --> 02:25:09,000
"And my name's Malfoy, Draco Malfoy."

4005
02:25:09,000 --> 02:25:10,560
Ron gave a slight cough,

4006
02:25:10,560 --> 02:25:12,440
which might have been hiding a snigget.

4007
02:25:12,439 --> 02:25:14,120
Draco Malfoy looked at him.

4008
02:25:14,120 --> 02:25:16,000
"Think my name's funny, do you?

4009
02:25:16,000 --> 02:25:17,680
No need to ask who you are.

4010
02:25:17,680 --> 02:25:20,360
My father told me all the Weasleys have red hair,

4011
02:25:20,359 --> 02:25:23,160
freckles, and more children than they can afford."

4012
02:25:23,160 --> 02:25:24,720
He turned back to Harry.

4013
02:25:24,720 --> 02:25:28,920
"You'll soon find out some wizarding 
families are much better than others, Potter.

4014
02:25:28,920 --> 02:25:31,640
You don't want to go making 
friends with the wrong sort.

4015
02:25:31,640 --> 02:25:32,880
I can help you there."

4016
02:25:32,880 --> 02:25:36,520
He held out his hand to shake 
Harry's, but Harry didn't take it.

4017
02:25:36,520 --> 02:25:39,360
"I think I can tell who the wrong 
sort are for myself, thanks,"

4018
02:25:39,359 --> 02:25:41,000
he said coolly.

4019
02:25:41,000 --> 02:25:43,040
Draco Malfoy didn't go red,

4020
02:25:43,040 --> 02:25:45,600
but a pink tinge appeared in his pale cheeks.

4021
02:25:45,600 --> 02:25:47,480
"I'd be careful if I were you, Potter,"

4022
02:25:47,479 --> 02:25:48,639
he said slowly.

4023
02:25:48,640 --> 02:25:52,000
"Unless you're a bit politer you'll 
go the same way as your parents.

4024
02:25:52,000 --> 02:25:54,439
They didn't know what was good for them, either.

4025
02:25:54,439 --> 02:25:57,439
You hang around with riffraff 
like the Weasleys and that Hagrid,

4026
02:25:57,439 --> 02:25:59,080
and it'll rub off on you."

4027
02:25:59,080 --> 02:26:00,960
Both Harry and Ron stood up.

4028
02:26:00,960 --> 02:26:01,840
"Say that again,"

4029
02:26:01,840 --> 02:26:04,680
Ron said, his face as red as his hair.

4030
02:26:04,680 --> 02:26:07,201
"Oh, you're going to fight us, are you?"

4031
02:26:07,200 --> 02:26:08,559
Malfoy sneered.

4032
02:26:08,560 --> 02:26:09,720
"Unless you get out now,"

4033
02:26:09,720 --> 02:26:10,560
said Harry,

4034
02:26:10,560 --> 02:26:12,241
more bravely than he felt,

4035
02:26:12,240 --> 02:26:15,679
because Crabbe and Goyle were 
a lot bigger than him or Ron.

4036
02:26:15,680 --> 02:26:17,241
"But we don't feet like leaving,

4037
02:26:17,240 --> 02:26:18,840
do we, boys?

4038
02:26:18,840 --> 02:26:21,840
We've eaten all our food and 
you still seem to have some."

4039
02:26:21,840 --> 02:26:26,120
Goyle reached toward the Chocolate 
Frogs next to Ron - Ron leapt forward,

4040
02:26:26,120 --> 02:26:28,439
but before he'd so much as touched Goyle,

4041
02:26:28,439 --> 02:26:30,359
Goyle let out a horrible yell.

4042
02:26:30,359 --> 02:26:32,799
Scabbers the rat was hanging off his finger,

4043
02:26:32,800 --> 02:26:36,080
sharp little teeth sunk deep 
into Goyle's knuckle - Crabbe

4044
02:26:36,080 --> 02:26:40,200
and Malfoy backed away as Goyle 
swung Scabbers round and round,

4045
02:26:40,200 --> 02:26:44,399
howling, and when Scabbets finally 
flew off and hit the window,

4046
02:26:44,399 --> 02:26:46,519
all three of them disappeared at once.

4047
02:26:46,520 --> 02:26:49,520
Perhaps they thought there were 
more rats lurking among the sweets,

4048
02:26:49,520 --> 02:26:51,440
or perhaps they'd heard footsteps,

4049
02:26:51,439 --> 02:26:52,719
because a second later,

4050
02:26:52,720 --> 02:26:54,760
Hermione Granger had come in.

4051
02:26:54,760 --> 02:26:55,960
"What has been going on?"

4052
02:26:55,960 --> 02:27:01,399
she said, looking at the sweets all over the 
floor and Ron picking up Scabbers by his tail.

4053
02:27:01,399 --> 02:27:02,519
I think he's been knocked out,

4054
02:27:02,520 --> 02:27:06,241
" Ron said to Harry. He 
looked closer at Scabbers. "

4055
02:27:06,240 --> 02:27:09,479
No , I don't believe it , 
he's gone back to sleep-"

4056
02:27:09,479 --> 02:27:10,639
And so he had.

4057
02:27:10,640 --> 02:27:12,320
"You've met Malfoy before?"

4058
02:27:12,319 --> 02:27:15,120
Harry explained about their 
meeting in Diagon Alley.

4059
02:27:15,120 --> 02:27:16,240
"I've heard of his family,"

4060
02:27:16,240 --> 02:27:17,559
said Ron darkly.

4061
02:27:17,560 --> 02:27:21,560
"They were some of the first to come back 
to our side after You-Know-Who disappeared.

4062
02:27:21,560 --> 02:27:23,121
Said they'd been bewitched.

4063
02:27:23,120 --> 02:27:24,720
My dad doesn't believe it.

4064
02:27:24,720 --> 02:27:29,000
He says Malfoy's father didn't need an 
excuse to go over to the Dark Side."

4065
02:27:29,000 --> 02:27:30,479
He turned to Hermione.

4066
02:27:30,479 --> 02:27:31,879
"Can we help you with something?"

4067
02:27:31,880 --> 02:27:34,520
"You'd better hurry up and put your robes on,

4068
02:27:34,520 --> 02:27:36,960
I've just been up to the 
front to ask the conductor,

4069
02:27:36,960 --> 02:27:38,720
and he says we're nearly there.

4070
02:27:38,720 --> 02:27:40,760
You haven't been fighting, have you?

4071
02:27:40,760 --> 02:27:43,120
You'll be in trouble before we even get there!"

4072
02:27:43,120 --> 02:27:45,399
"Scabbers has been fighting, not us,"

4073
02:27:45,399 --> 02:27:47,479
said Ron, scowling at her.

4074
02:27:47,479 --> 02:27:49,439
"Would you mind leaving while we change?"

4075
02:27:49,439 --> 02:27:50,240
"All right ,

4076
02:27:50,240 --> 02:27:54,240
I only came in here because people 
outside are behaving very childishly,

4077
02:27:54,240 --> 02:27:56,319
racing up and down the corridors,"

4078
02:27:56,319 --> 02:27:58,399
said Hermione in a sniffy voice.

4079
02:27:58,399 --> 02:28:01,519
"And you've got dirt on your 
nose, by the way, did you know?"

4080
02:28:01,520 --> 02:28:03,360
Ron glared at her as she left.

4081
02:28:03,359 --> 02:28:05,080
Harry peered out of the window.

4082
02:28:05,080 --> 02:28:06,399
It was getting dark.

4083
02:28:06,399 --> 02:28:09,759
He could see mountains and 
forests under a deep purple sky.

4084
02:28:09,760 --> 02:28:12,000
The train did seem to be slowing down.

4085
02:28:12,000 --> 02:28:15,640
He and Ron took off their jackets 
and pulled on their long black robes.

4086
02:28:15,640 --> 02:28:17,400
Ron's were a bit short for him,

4087
02:28:17,399 --> 02:28:19,479
you could see his sneakers underneath them.

4088
02:28:19,479 --> 02:28:21,240
A voice echoed through the train:

4089
02:28:21,240 --> 02:28:24,240
"We will be reaching Hogwarts 
in five minutes' time.

4090
02:28:24,240 --> 02:28:26,040
Please leave your luggage on the train,

4091
02:28:26,040 --> 02:28:28,200
it will be taken to the school separately."

4092
02:28:28,200 --> 02:28:30,359
Harry's stomach lurched with nerves and Ron,

4093
02:28:30,359 --> 02:28:33,000
he saw, looked pale under his freckles.

4094
02:28:33,000 --> 02:28:35,359
They crammed their pockets 
with the last of the sweets

4095
02:28:35,359 --> 02:28:38,000
and joined the crowd thronging the corridor.

4096
02:28:38,000 --> 02:28:40,840
The train slowed right down and finally stopped.

4097
02:28:40,840 --> 02:28:43,880
People pushed their way toward 
the door and out on to a tiny,

4098
02:28:43,880 --> 02:28:45,080
dark platform.

4099
02:28:45,080 --> 02:28:47,160
Harry shivered in the cold night air.

4100
02:28:47,160 --> 02:28:49,840
Then a lamp came bobbing over 
the heads of the students,

4101
02:28:49,840 --> 02:28:51,840
and Harry heard a familiar voice:

4102
02:28:51,840 --> 02:28:56,200
"Firs' years! Firs' years over 
here! All right there, Harry?"

4103
02:28:56,200 --> 02:28:59,319
Hagrid's big hairy face 
beamed over the sea of heads.

4104
02:28:59,319 --> 02:29:00,840
"C'mon, follow me ,

4105
02:29:00,840 --> 02:29:02,360
any more firs' years?

4106
02:29:02,359 --> 02:29:04,000
Mind yer step, now!

4107
02:29:04,000 --> 02:29:06,160
Firs' years follow me!"

4108
02:29:06,160 --> 02:29:07,439
Slipping and stumbling,

4109
02:29:07,439 --> 02:29:10,639
they followed Hagrid down 
what seemed to be a steep,

4110
02:29:10,640 --> 02:29:11,760
narrow path.

4111
02:29:11,760 --> 02:29:16,000
It was so dark on either side of them that 
Harry thought there must be thick trees there.

4112
02:29:16,000 --> 02:29:17,439
Nobody spoke much.

4113
02:29:17,439 --> 02:29:20,120
Neville, the boy who kept losing his toad,

4114
02:29:20,120 --> 02:29:21,720
sniffed once or twice.

4115
02:29:21,720 --> 02:29:24,600
"Ye' all get yer firs' 
sight o' Hogwarts in a sec,"

4116
02:29:24,600 --> 02:29:26,400
Hagrid called over his shoulder,

4117
02:29:26,399 --> 02:29:27,920
"jus' round this bend here."

4118
02:29:27,920 --> 02:29:28,800
There was a loud

4119
02:29:28,800 --> 02:29:29,600
"Oooooh!"

4120
02:29:29,600 --> 02:29:34,241
The narrow path had opened suddenly 
onto the edge of a great black take.

4121
02:29:34,240 --> 02:29:36,719
Perched atop a high mountain on the other side,

4122
02:29:36,720 --> 02:29:38,880
its windows sparkling in the starry sky,

4123
02:29:38,880 --> 02:29:42,040
was a vast castle with many turrets and towers.

4124
02:29:42,040 --> 02:29:43,840
"No more'n four to a boat!"

4125
02:29:43,840 --> 02:29:44,840
Hagrid called,

4126
02:29:44,840 --> 02:29:48,279
pointing to a fleet of little boats 
sitting in the water by the shore.

4127
02:29:48,279 --> 02:29:51,800
Harry and Ron were followed into 
their boat by Neville and Hermione.

4128
02:29:51,800 --> 02:29:52,520
"Everyone in?"

4129
02:29:52,520 --> 02:29:55,241
shouted Hagrid, who had a boat to himself.

4130
02:29:55,240 --> 02:29:56,559
"Right then , FORWARD!"

4131
02:29:56,560 --> 02:29:59,201
And the fleet of little 
boats moved off all at once,

4132
02:29:59,200 --> 02:30:00,599
gliding across the lake,

4133
02:30:00,600 --> 02:30:02,600
which was as smooth as glass.

4134
02:30:02,600 --> 02:30:03,840
Everyone was silent,

4135
02:30:03,840 --> 02:30:06,360
staring up at the great castle overhead.

4136
02:30:06,359 --> 02:30:10,519
It towered over them as they sailed nearer 
and nearer to the cliff on which it stood.

4137
02:30:10,520 --> 02:30:11,520
"Heads down!"

4138
02:30:11,520 --> 02:30:14,280
yelled Hagrid as the first 
boats reached the cliff;

4139
02:30:14,279 --> 02:30:15,439
they all bent their heads

4140
02:30:15,439 --> 02:30:19,000
and the little boats carried them through 
a curtain of ivy that hid a wide opening

4141
02:30:19,000 --> 02:30:20,279
in the cliff face.

4142
02:30:20,279 --> 02:30:22,200
They were carried along a dark tunnel,

4143
02:30:22,200 --> 02:30:24,840
which seemed to be taking them 
right underneath the castle,

4144
02:30:24,840 --> 02:30:27,200
until they reached a kind of underground harbor,

4145
02:30:27,200 --> 02:30:29,960
where they clambered out onto rocks and pebbles.

4146
02:30:29,960 --> 02:30:32,560
"Oy, you there! Is this your toad?"

4147
02:30:32,560 --> 02:30:33,560
said Hagrid,

4148
02:30:33,560 --> 02:30:36,280
who was checking the boats as 
people climbed out of them.

4149
02:30:36,279 --> 02:30:37,040
"Trevor!"

4150
02:30:37,040 --> 02:30:38,279
cried Neville blissfully,

4151
02:30:38,279 --> 02:30:39,840
holding out his hands.

4152
02:30:39,840 --> 02:30:43,279
Then they clambered up a passageway 
in the rock after Hagrid's lamp,

4153
02:30:43,279 --> 02:30:45,200
coming out at last onto smooth,

4154
02:30:45,200 --> 02:30:47,760
damp grass right in the shadow of the castle.

4155
02:30:47,760 --> 02:30:51,000
They walked up a flight of stone 
steps and crowded around the huge,

4156
02:30:51,000 --> 02:30:52,240
Oak front door.

4157
02:30:52,240 --> 02:30:55,399
"Everyone here? You there, still got yer toad?"

4158
02:30:55,399 --> 02:30:58,960
Hagrid raised a gigantic fist and 
knocked three times on the castle door.

